                  </persName>
            , Purser."</p>
               <p>"The Commissioners for Victualling his Majesty's Navy, London."</p>
               <p>"I do hereby certify that the above bill is drawn for the services therein expressed, and by my order,</p>
               <p>"A. R. KERR, Captain."</p>
               <p>With intention to defraud our Sovereign Lord the King, against the statute.</p>
               <p>SECOND COUNT. For feloniously uttering and publishing as true a like forged bill of exchange, with the like intent.</p>
