            . I was acting lieutenant of his Majesty's ship Acasta. I have examined the signatures</p>
               <p>"John Trevarton and A. R. Kerr," affixed to this bill. I am well acquainted with Captain 
               <persName id="t18151025-116-person1062">Kerr</persName>
            's and Mr. Trevarton's hand writings, and neither the one nor the other of these signatures is either of their hand writings.</p>
               <p>- TULLY. I have had various opportunities of observing Captain Kerr and Mr. Trevarton write their signatures. Neither of these names written on this bill is either of their hand writings.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18151025-116-person1063">
